settings.title: Athlete Spotlight
settings.name: Betsi Flint
settings.description:
Betsi began her beach volleyball career at Loyola Marymount University where she played two years indoor volleyball and two years on the beach team. In 2015, Betsi, with then partner, Kelley Larsen, became the youngest team to ever win an AVP tournament in Cincinnati.

Besti has back-to-back AVP wins this season winning in Seattle and San Francisco with partner Emily Day. She joined team JOLYN in the fall of 2017 and has her eyes on the 2020 Tokyo games. We're proud to have her on team JOLYN and call her a JoPro!
